The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper considers the unique features of millimeter wave communications, such as directional beamforming and LOS/NLOS channels, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper specifically focuses on finite mmWave networks, which falls under the Mobile Computing (cs.MM) sub-category.
